     <!--mstheme--></font></h2> <h2 align="center">
    <!--mstheme--><font color="#CC0000"><b>AS1 Seismic System <br> </b><a href="AS1stationmapNew1204.gif"> <img border="2" src="AS1stationmapNew1204_small.gif" xthumbnail-orig-image="AS1stationmapNew1204.gif" width="100" height="79"></a>
     <!--mstheme--></font></h2> <p>The AS1 seismic system is sold by Jeff Batten, who is <a href="http://www.amateurseismologist.com"> THE AMATEUR SEISMOLOGIST</a>, 2470 Stearns St. #322, Simi Valley, Ca. 93063.&nbsp; Contact: <a href="mailto:amateurseismo@gmail.com">amateurseismo@gmail.com</a> </p> <p>Each year <a href="http://www.iris.edu/">IRIS</a> runs a workshop at which teachers learn the basics of seismology and how to run an AS-1 seismic system.&nbsp; For more information, see:&nbsp; <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/programs/education_and_outreach/seismographs_in_schools"> http://www.iris.edu/hq/programs/education_and_outreach/seismographs_in_schools</a> </p> <h3>
    <!--mstheme--><font color="#CC0000"><a href="faq/index.html">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</a> 
     <!--mstheme--></font></h3> <h3>
    <!--mstheme--><font color="#CC0000"><b>Specifications:</b>
     <!--mstheme--></font></h3> </font>
  <blockquote>
   <font face="Comic Sans MS, Arial, Helvetica"> <p align="left"><b>Seismometer:</b> Vertical velocity transducer with oil damping.<br> <b>Natural Period:</b> 1.5 sec (Filter extends bandwidth to 20 sec.)<br> <b>Amplifier:</b> 100db w/Low Pass Filter -- there is a zero adjustment but no gain adjustment.<br> <b>Digitizer:</b> 12 Bit Analog to Digital Converter<br> <b>Bandwidth:</b> .5 sec to 20 sec&nbsp;<br> <b>Dimensions:</b> 17" Long, 6" Wide, 10.5" High</p> 
    <!--mstheme--></font>
   <table border="1" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" width="37%" bordercolordark="#006600" bordercolorlight="#009900"> 
    <tbody>
     <tr> 
      <td width="12%">
